   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">In normal operation the rectifier supplies
the inverter and charges the battery. The inverter supplies the load.</p>
         <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">In normal operation the inverter supplies the load.</p>
         <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">The rectifier mains input feeds the phase angle
controlled rectifier via a matching transformer and converts the AC
to DC. The rectifier maintains a constant DC by compensating for both
variations in the input voltage and load.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The inverter converts
the DC to AC with optimized sine wave pulse width control (PWM).</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with a bypass:</b> If the inverter is unavailable
or overloaded (by default, load at 150% for more than 1 minute or
load at 125% for more than 10 minutes), the system will change to
bypass operation. For more information see chapter <xref href="Bypass_Operation_System_Operation_CPT_0000319410.dita"
                  format="dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="concept"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with manual bypass switches:</b> When
the load is supplied in normal operation the manual bypass switch
is always in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position.</p>
